        "text": "Post by CrepedCrusader on\n\nVictor Salva is a writer and director behind such films as Powder (1996),and the Jeepers Creepers franchise. While filming his feature directorial debut, Clownhouse (1989), Salva molested the 12-year-old star of the film, Nathan Forrest Winters. When Salva was arrested, not only was he in possession of videos capturing the sexual abuse of Winters, but also other commercially produced child sexual abuse material. The arrest happened before the dubbing was done for the film. Post-arrest, the victim (Winters) did the dubbing at Francis Ford Coppola's house, who was an executive producer on the film. In a 2018 interview, Winters claimed that during this time, he was told he would never work again in the business. He also claimed Francis Ford Coppola sued him for breach of contract. Salva was sentenced to three years in prison, but served only fifteen months. In 1995, Salva returned to filmmaking with the sleeper hit Powder, with a cast that included Mary Steenburgen and Jeff Goldblum. Winters and others protested outside the premier of the film. Some might think a sexual abuse victim picketing outside a movie premier would dissuade people from giving Salva more work, but in 2001, Salva wrote and directed the minor hit Jeepers Creepers, which would go on to spawn sequels written/directed by Salva in 2003 and 2017. (Francis Ford Coppola served as executing producer on the first two Jeepers movies.) Salva has also made a few other movies over the years, but these have received far less attention than Powder and the Jeepers films.\n\nPost by moviebuffbrad on\n\nHow does a rapist/pedophile keep getting work in Hollywood?\n\nThe world may never know.\n\nI suppose at least this guy did his \"time\", unlike Polanski. The surprise here was how big a piece of shit Coppola is. I knew he produced the Jeepers Creepers movies, but damn.\n\nPost by moviebuffbrad on\n\nI don't know, but probably better he stays busy.\n\nJust don't allow him to work on movies that have any kids in them.\n\nThey couldn't even do that, JP2 opens with a young boy getting snatched up by the titular \"Creeper\". That movie is also infamous for the copious amounts of shirtless high school boy scenes. Granted, most of these guys were 20 something year old actors, but at least one of them was 16.\n\nA lot of people read subtext into the movie that it's about Salva grappling with his own demons. There's a high sexual component to the Creeper, particularly the scene where he chooses his victims by winking at them and licking on the window. Every single one of them is male, of course.\n\nPost by moviemouth on\n\nI don't know, but probably better he stays busy.\n\nJust don't allow him to work on movies that have any kids in them.\n\nThey couldn't even do that, JP2 opens with a young boy getting snatched up by the titular \"Creeper\". That movie is also infamous for the copious amounts of shirtless high school boy scenes. Granted, most of these guys were 20 something year old actors, but at least one of them was 16.\n\nA lot of people read subtext into the movie that it's about Salva grappling with his own demons. There's a high sexual component to the Creeper, particularly the scene where he chooses his victims by winking at them and licking on the window. Every single one of them is male, of course.\n\nAll I can say is I hope that boy had a parent that was keeping a close eye on them and not allowing Silva to be around him alone.\n\nThe subtext makes sense considering what we know about Silva.\n\nPost by CrepedCrusader on\n\nHeâ€™s a fucking monster.\n\nFrom his wikipedia page:\n\nWhen asked about the controversy surrounding Powder, Salva said, \"This has followed me around ever since it happened, but once people meet me the phantoms go away and they realize I made a stupid mistake, years ago. ... My past is going to follow me around for as long as people want to talk about it.\"\n\nDefinitely a piece of crap."
